article.headline: McBride's touch at foul line lifts Syracuse
article.linkText: Syracuse snaps four-game slide up upsetting BC
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Julie McBride went 9-of-10 from the free-throw
line in the final 53 seconds and finished with 23 points Saturday
to lead Syracuse to a 76-71 win over Boston College (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP).

	   Shannon Perry added 19 points and eight rebounds for the
Orangewomen (6-10, 1-4 Big East), who snapped a four-game losing
streak. Rochelle Coleman chipped in with 15 points.

	   Amber Jacobs paced Boston College (11-4, 3-1) with 20 points.
Becky Gottstein had 16 points and 16 rebounds.

	   The loss snapped BC's four-game win streak and halted a 15-game
home winning streak.

	   After the Eagles took a 38-37 lead on Gottstein's free throw
with 17:39 to go, the Orangewomen took charge with a 17-7 run in
the next 4:30.

	   Perry scored the first six points in the run and Coleman capped
it with a 3-pointer from the top of the key, making it 54-45 with
12:52 left.

	   The Eagles, who moved back into the Top 25 after being out for
one week, did not get closer than seven points until a late charge
closed it to three with 5 seconds left.

	   McBride sealed it by hitting two free throws.

	   Syracuse, which shot 65 percent in the first half, used a 12-2
run to close the first half and take a 37-31 at the break.
